p: Mrs. Mary Jane Whitesides the above named defendant being first duly sworn deposes and says. That she has heard read the foregoing Answer of Return to the application for a writ of Habeas Corpus, and Known the contents thereof and that the same is true of her own knowledge of such matters as are therein stated on information and belief and as to those matters she believes therein to be true.
Inscribed to before me this 2nd day of January AD 1866.
